<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>Condo App Launcher Cloud Implementation Plan</title>
    <style>
      body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; margin: 36px; color: #0f172a; }
      h1, h2 { color: #0f172a; }
      h1 { margin-bottom: 8px; }
      h2 { margin-top: 24px; }
      p, li { line-height: 1.5; }
      table { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; margin-top: 12px; }
      th, td { border: 1px solid #cbd5e1; padding: 8px; text-align: left; }
      th { background: #e2e8f0; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Condo App Launcher Cloud Implementation Plan</h1>
    <p>
      Build the Electron launcher architecture on AWS first while preserving a clean path to Azure and Google Cloud.
    </p>

    <h2>Recommended implementation steps</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Document the Electron launcher workflow and backend API contract.</li>
      <li>Keep Docker as the packaging baseline with multi-architecture image builds.</li>
      <li>Launch an AWS-first backend with ECR, S3, API Gateway, Lambda, Cognito, and DynamoDB.</li>
      <li>Add CloudWatch logging, alarms, and Secrets Manager-based secret storage.</li>
      <li>Create CI/CD pipelines for Docker images and Electron installers.</li>
      <li>Introduce queued remote operations such as restart, diagnostics, and shutdown.</li>
      <li>Abstract infrastructure with Terraform modules for Azure and Google Cloud parity.</li>
      <li>Adopt managed databases and provider-native automation as requirements grow.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Cloud service mapping</h2>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Capability</th>
          <th>AWS</th>
          <th>Azure</th>
          <th>Google Cloud</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Container registry</td>
          <td>ECR</td>
          <td>Azure Container Registry</td>
          <td>Artifact Registry</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Serverless API</td>
          <td>API Gateway + Lambda</td>
          <td>API Management + Azure Functions</td>
          <td>API Gateway + Cloud Functions</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Container runtime</td>
          <td>ECS Fargate</td>
          <td>Azure Container Apps</td>
          <td>Cloud Run</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Identity</td>
          <td>Cognito</td>
          <td>Microsoft Entra External ID</td>
          <td>Identity Platform</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>NoSQL state store</td>
          <td>DynamoDB</td>
          <td>Cosmos DB</td>
          <td>Firestore</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Queue/eventing</td>
          <td>SQS + EventBridge</td>
          <td>Service Bus + Event Grid</td>
          <td>Pub/Sub + Eventarc</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Secrets</td>
          <td>Secrets Manager</td>
          <td>Key Vault</td>
          <td>Secret Manager</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Observability</td>
          <td>CloudWatch</td>
          <td>Azure Monitor</td>
          <td>Cloud Logging</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>Delivery phases</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Phase 1: local launcher orchestration plus cloud auth, config, and updates.</li>
      <li>Phase 2: remote callable actions, machine registration, and diagnostics uploads.</li>
      <li>Phase 3: managed databases, scheduled maintenance, and tenant-aware automation.</li>
      <li>Phase 4: multi-region resilience and optional multi-cloud failover.</li>
    </ul>
  </body>
</html>
